# Code review ‚Äî RMS-specific checklist

Apply this file in review mode (when the `pr-review-stage1` / `pr-review-stage2` skill is triggered or the user requests a PR review). Covers only what cannot be inferred from general principles: project invariants from `docs/knowledge/` and `docs/planning/`. Check general concerns (readability, tests, security) in parallel at your discretion.

Source of truth for each item: `docs/knowledge/sync-protocol.md`, `docs/knowledge/hybrid-plan-model.md`, `docs/knowledge/offline-first-sync.md`, `docs/planning/sprint-1.md`. If a change intentionally modifies an invariant ‚Äî the corresponding document must be updated in the same PR.

## 1. Sync protocol

| What to look for | Why it is a bug |
|---|---|
| `uuid.New()` / `gen_random_uuid()` / `RETURNING id` for project, plan, room, wall, photo | ID is an echo of the client UUID v7, see sync-protocol ¬ß2 |
| LWW comparison against `time.Now()`, `now()`, `current_timestamp` instead of `clientUpdatedAt` | LWW compares the client timestamp, not arrival time |
| `c.JSON(409, ‚Ä¶)`, `huma.Status409Conflict` in the `/sync/push` handler | Push always responds 200 partial-success; conflicts go in `conflicts[]` |
| `errors[]` returned without a machine-readable `reason` (`validation \| notFound \| forbidden \| unknown`) | The `ErrorItem` contract is fixed |
| `DELETE FROM <sync table>` in SQL/Go | Soft-delete only: `SET deleted_at = now()` |
| Pull query with `WHERE deleted_at IS NULL` | Pull must return tombstones |
| SELECT on a sync table without `WHERE workspace_id = $N` | Data leak between workspaces |
| `SyncCursor` incremented in Go code or via `EXTRACT(EPOCH ‚Ä¶)` | Only via trigger on SEQUENCE `sync_cursor_seq` |
| `clientOpId` used as an entity identifier (or vice versa) | These are different fields; `clientOpId` is unique per operation |

## 2. Schema / migrations

- New file `002_*.sql`, `003_*.sql` before release ‚Üí violates `goose-dev-migrations`. Changes only in `001_init.sql` + `just db-reset`.
- A new sync table **must** have: `id TEXT PRIMARY KEY`, `workspace_id TEXT NOT NULL REFERENCES workspaces(id)`, `updated_at TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now()`, `sync_cursor BIGINT NOT NULL DEFAULT nextval('sync_cursor_seq')`, `deleted_at TIMESTAMPTZ`, and a `BEFORE INSERT OR UPDATE` trigger to bump `sync_cursor`.
- `UUID` column instead of `TEXT` for a sync entity id ‚Üí bug (must accommodate client UUID v7).
- Any manual edit to `apps/api/internal/db/*.go` or `packages/api-contracts/types.gen.ts` ‚Üí bug (generated files).

## 3. Plan / Room / Wall

- Room names, wall materials, any metadata inside `Plan.payloadJson` ‚Üí violates hybrid model. Must live in `rooms` / `walls`.
- Coordinates, lengths, corner graph edges in relational columns ‚Üí violates the model.
- Server endpoint returning a "full plan with all rooms and walls as one JSON" ‚Üí violation: merging is client-only.
- Plan/room/wall synchronized as one aggregate (one `sync_cursor` for all three) ‚Üí violation.

## 4. Auth

- `workspaceId` taken from request body, query string, or path parameter ‚Üí bug. Only from JWT via middleware.
- Handler parses the `Authorization` header itself or calls `jwt.Parse(...)` ‚Üí bug; must go through middleware.
- Field `expiresIn` appears in `/auth/sign-in` or `/auth/refresh` response ‚Üí bug (contract is fixed: TTL is read from `exp` claim).
- Refresh token stored as plaintext in `refresh_tokens` ‚Üí bug (must be argon2/bcrypt hash).

## 5. Photo upload

- Endpoint parsing `multipart/form-data` for photos ‚Üí violation (pre-signed PUT only).
- `photoId` generated on the server (e.g. in `POST /photos/upload-url`) ‚Üí bug; client sets it.
- Any image processing on the server (resize, thumbnail, EXIF-strip) in sprint 1 ‚Üí out of scope.

## 6. Web ‚Üî API

- `interface ProjectDto`, `interface PullResponse` etc. in `apps/web/src/` duplicating types from `types.gen.ts` ‚Üí bug (single source of truth is `types.gen.ts`).
- Direct `fetch('/api/v1/...')`, `axios.get('/api/v1/...')` bypassing the wrapper in `src/api/` ‚Üí bug.
- `openapi.yaml` changed without `just api-gen` in the same commit ‚Üí bug (TS client is stale).
- `openapi.yaml` changed without syncing `apps/api/internal/sync/types.go` ‚Üí bug (Go types out of sync; no Go codegen).

## 7. Architectural layers

- `http.Error(w, ...)` in middleware or handlers ‚Üí bug (violates OpenAPI contract, returns text/plain instead of JSON). Errors must go through Huma.
- SQL strings in a Go handler without a corresponding file in `apps/api/queries/` ‚Üí violates `sqlc-queries`.
- `pgx.Conn`/`pgxpool.Pool` directly in a handler bypassing the generated `db.Queries` ‚Üí violates the layer contract.
- Direct write to `http.ResponseWriter` inside a huma handler ‚Üí violates `go-http-handlers`.
- `panic` in request path ‚Üí violates `go-error-handling`.
- Two write paths for the same entity (handler + background worker both writing to the same table via different SQL) ‚Üí violates `no-hacks`, single source of truth.
- Boolean flags (`isSyncing`, `loaded`, `initialized`) without a documented contract in a comment or doc ‚Üí violates `no-hacks`.
- Logic for multiple sync entities (project, plan, room, wall, photo) in one handler file instead of separate files per entity ‚Üí architectural smell. Rule: `internal/handler/sync/push.go` contains only shared utilities and the `applyPushOperation` dispatcher; each entity's logic lives in a separate `push_<entity>.go`. Same applies to pull if it grows similarly.

## 8. Breaking changes for clients

- Existing field removed from an OpenAPI response ‚Üí break.
- Existing field type changed (e.g. `int32` ‚Üí `int64`, `string` ‚Üí `enum`) ‚Üí break.
- Existing request field made `required` (was `optional`) ‚Üí break for old clients.
- Validation tightened (`maxLength`, `pattern`) for an existing field without agreement ‚Üí potential break.
- `EntityType` literal removed or renamed (`project | plan | room | wall | photo`) ‚Üí break. Adding new values is fine.
- `reason` literal in `ConflictItem` / `ErrorItem` removed or renamed ‚Üí break.
- `cursor` format changed (e.g. was `int64`, now `string`) ‚Üí break.

If a PR breaks any of the above ‚Äî require an API versioning discussion in a comment.

## 9. Documentation

- PR changes the sync contract but `docs/knowledge/sync-protocol.md` is not updated ‚Üí bug.
- PR changes the `plans`/`rooms`/`walls` schema or geometry model but `docs/knowledge/hybrid-plan-model.md` is not updated ‚Üí bug.
- PR closes an "open question" from `docs/planning/sprint-1.md` ¬ß5 but does not mark it resolved ‚Üí incomplete.

## 10. Architecture Decision Records (ADR)

The decision log lives in `docs/adr/` (index in `docs/adr/README.md`). During review verify the PR against the ADR list from two directions:

**1. PR relies on an existing ADR ‚Äî it must be respected.**

| What to look for | Which ADR |
|---|---|
| Changes to `Justfile` recipes `check`, `check-coverage`, `_api-coverage-threshold`; new test files with/without `//go:build integration`; edits to `api_coverage_min_pct`; adding paths to the coverage filter | [`0001-testing-baseline.md`](../docs/adr/0001-testing-baseline.md) |

If a PR contradicts an ADR decision (e.g. a test with a Postgres dependency lacking the build tag, or `api_coverage_min_pct` lowered without explanation) ‚Äî that is a bug. Either bring the code into compliance, or update the ADR in the same PR with a new Status and reason.

**2. PR introduces an architecturally significant decision but no ADR exists.**

Signs that a decision requires an ADR (not just code):

- A **cross-cutting mechanism** is added or changed affecting multiple layers (new auth, caching, queue, invalidation, background job approach).
- A **new external dependency** is introduced (DB, broker, object storage, runtime) or an existing one is replaced.
- An **invariant or contract** is established that future PRs must respect (ID format, time format, soft-delete rules, shared CI threshold).
- A **trade-off fork** is resolved where alternatives have merit and the choice must be recorded (e.g. pre-signed PUT vs multipart, sqlc vs ORM, hybrid Plan vs normalized schema).

If these signals are present and no new file in `docs/adr/` is in the PR ‚Äî require an ADR in the same PR. Otherwise nobody will remember why this decision was made a month later.

ADR is short: **Status**, **Context**, **Decision**, **Consequences**. No copied guides or philosophy ‚Äî that goes in `docs/knowledge/`.
